# Project Report: Digital Ambassador Tasks

## Task 1: Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic
**Tool Used:** Canva  
**Description:** For this task, I designed a one-page infographic titled "Digital Success for Students." The design uses a clean, modern aesthetic with a blue and white color palette to convey professionalism. It covers three core pillars: **Digital Tools** (highlighting Notion and Google Workspace), **Safe Internet Practices** (emphasizing 2FA and privacy settings), and **Email Etiquette** (focusing on clear subject lines and professional sign-offs). I used icons to make the information scannable, ensuring that a student could grasp the "why" behind digital literacy in under 30 seconds.

**Reflection:**
What I found most interesting while making this was the challenge of "visual hierarchy." I initially tried to include too much text, but I realized that an effective infographic relies on icons and short, punchy headlines to keep the audience engaged. Balancing the aesthetic elements with factual information was a great exercise in communication design.

